<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 2 GANG MEMBERS SENTENCED IN KILLING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two gang members were sentenced to prison terms Tuesday for the 1989 murder of 
an 18-year-old Tujunga man. 
</P>
<P>
Hector Hernandez, 19, of Sun Valley and Efren Alavarez, 20, of North Hollywood 
pleaded guilty July 23 to killing Thomas Francis Langton as he ran from a Sun 
Valley party in May, 1989. 
</P>
<P>
According to police reports, Langton was at a party in the 7500 block of 
Cartwright Avenue when he was chased and attacked by a group of youths believed 
to be gang members. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Langton was beaten and kicked by the youths before he was shot 
several times in the upper torso. 
</P>
<P>
Alavarez, the gunman in the incident, was sentenced to 17 years to life in 
state prison for second-degree murder. 
</P>
<P>
Hernandez was sentenced to seven years for voluntary manslaughter. 
</P>
