<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Kenneth Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Huntington Beach Art Center will receive about $30,000 from the recent 
4-day equestrian fund-raising event. 
</P>
<P>
That brings to about $125,000 the amount raised toward a $750,000 goal needed 
to begin refurbishing of an 11,000-square-foot facility to house the proposed 
community arts center, slated to open in 1991. A free, informal open house and 
tours will be held at the site Thursday, Friday and Saturday. Staff members 
will discuss program plans and answer questions. Hours are Thursday, 4 to 7 
p.m.; Friday, 4 to 8 p.m.; and Saturday, 11 a.m. to 3 p.m. The facility is at 
538 Main St., Huntington Beach. Information: (714) 536-5258. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
