<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OJAI; 
</P>
<P>
MAN CHECKING ATTIC WIRES ELECTROCUTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Oxnard electrician checking wires in the attic of an Ojai house Tuesday 
apparently electrocuted himself, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The 43-year-old man, who was working in a house in the 600 block of Del Norte 
Road, sent his partner to pick up some parts about 5 p.m. When the partner 
returned, he found the man dead with electrical burns on his face, chest and 
right hand, said Lt. Joe Funchess of the Ventura County Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
The Ventura County coroner's office could not release the victim's name Tuesday 
evening. KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
