<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Circle K Closing 201 Stores: The Circle K convenience store chain said it has 
begun closing 201 unprofitable stores and will complete the job by the end of 
the month. 
</P>
<P>
The move is intended to help turn around the Phoenix-based company, which in 
May filed for protection from creditors under Chapter 11 of federal bankruptcy 
law. Thirteen stores will be closed in Southern California, all in San Diego, 
Riverside and San Bernardino counties. Another 16 stores will be closed in 
Central and Northern California. Circle K now has about 550 stores in 
California, including 87 in Los Angeles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
