<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
BODY FOUND IN O.C. RESERVOIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The body of an unidentified man was found floating in a Trabuco Canyon 
reservoir early this morning, the Orange County Sheriff's Department said. 
</P>
<P>
It was unclear how long the man had been floating face down in the middle of 
the reservoir near Trabuco Canyon Road and Plano Trabuco Road, Sheriff's 
Department spokesman Richard J. Olson said. 
</P>
<P>
But he may have accidentally drowned while swimming in the reservoir sometime 
last night, Olson said. The 250-by-100-foot reservoir is used to supply water 
to a local nursery. 
</P>
<P>
A pile of clothing and personal belongings were found nearby at about 7 a.m. 
today, Olson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
