<HEADLINE>
<P>
SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
GRAHAM, BRYAN GET TENNIS HONOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TRUMBULL, Conn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Debbie Graham of Stanford and Steve Bryan of Texas-Austin were named college 
players of the year today by Tennis magazine and Volvo. 
</P>
<P>
Both won the NCAA singles championships this year. 
</P>
<P>
Graham, a junior from Fountain Valley, won the women's title with six 
straight-set victories and has a 52-0 record in singles matches. Bryan, a 
sophomore, has 53 singles victories. He turned pro in July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
